Work in institutions or enterprises by raising and solving different economic problems. The practice ends with defending a paper. For defending, the student submits a report containing an economic issue raised and solved during the practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the practice is to provide students with the possibility to integrate theoretical knowledge gained in master programme into real situations and problem solving processes of an enterprise or institution and thereby develop practical skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1)  understand difference and similarities of designers' and entrepreneurs' roles; 2) is acquainted with different possibilities of applying theoretical knowledge into practice; 3) can study respective problems and apply appropriate methods, including career planning; 4) sees opportunities and challenges in economic environment and complies design brief based on them; 5) can analyse business plan based on design audit and environmental analysis; 6) can conduct user research; 7) can lead or work as member of a creative team.
